---
import SimplePage from '../../layouts/SimplePage.astro';
import ServicesInquiryForm from '../../components/ServicesInquiryForm.astro';
import { CONTACT, GITHUB_USERNAME } from '../../consts';
import { hrefAbout, hrefBlog, hrefContact, hrefHome } from '../../utils/sitePaths';

const pathname = Astro.url.pathname;
const thanks = Astro.url.searchParams.has('thanks');
---

<SimplePage
	title="Services — Brian Gates"
	description="Contract consulting and implementation: software development, infrastructure, observability, web design, hosting, and automation."
>
	<h1 class="display-6 fw-bold border-bottom pb-3 mb-4">Services</h1>

	{
		thanks && (
			<div class="alert alert-success mb-4" role="status">
				Thanks — your services inquiry was sent. I will follow up by email soon.
			</div>
		)
	}

	<p class="lead text-body-secondary">
		I am <strong>open to contract engagements</strong> — from short advisory engagements and architecture reviews
		to implementation planning and hands-on engineering. If you need someone who can connect operations,
		infrastructure, and application code, I would be glad to discuss fit.
	</p>
	<p>
		Work can be structured as fixed-scope projects, ongoing part-time support, or focused engagements (for example:
		observability design, storage and platform work, or custom software and automation). I adapt to your existing
		tools, runbooks, and compliance requirements.
	</p>

	<h2 class="h4 fw-bold mt-5 mb-3">Areas I work in</h2>
	<ul class="mb-4">
		<li>
			<strong>Consulting services</strong> — Advisory and planning: architecture reviews, technology and platform
			choices, migration and cutover strategy, operational readiness, and documentation. Engagements can be short
			workshops, fixed-scope assessments, or ongoing guidance alongside your team.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Implementation services</strong> — Hands-on delivery against agreed scope: build-out, configuration,
			integration, cutovers, automation, and validation. I work within your change windows, tooling, and compliance
			expectations so outcomes land in production, not only on paper.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Web design, management &amp; hosting</strong> — Modern, performant static sites and small-business
			web presence; ongoing <strong>content and technical management</strong> (updates, DNS, TLS, performance);
			<strong>hosting</strong> guidance and implementation aligned with your environment — GitHub Pages, VPS, or
			managed providers. Suited to teams that want a site that remains straightforward to operate and evolve.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Networking</strong> — Enterprise and campus design and operations; <strong>Cisco</strong> routing
			and switching; <strong>UniFi</strong> / Ubiquiti Wi‑Fi and site design; monitoring and troubleshooting. I
			have <strong>led enterprise migrations from Cisco to UniFi</strong> — planning, parallel run, cutover, and
			handoff so teams land on stable Wi‑Fi and switching with clear documentation.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Virtualization &amp; platforms</strong> — <strong>VMware</strong> vSphere environments;
			<strong>Proxmox VE</strong> clusters, storage, and automation; integration with backup and monitoring
			stacks. I have planned and executed an <strong>enterprise VMware to Proxmox VE migration</strong> end to
			end — discovery, storage mapping, cutover, and validation.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Storage / SAN</strong> — Hands-on with <strong>Dell EMC VNX5300</strong>, <strong>Pure Storage</strong>,
			<strong>HPE Nimble</strong>, <strong>QNAP</strong>, <strong>TrueNAS</strong>, and similar platforms across
			block, appliance, and unified storage; VMware and Proxmox integration, migrations, and capacity planning.
			Comfortable coordinating with vendors and internal teams on performance and change windows.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Development &amp; custom tooling</strong> — Application and systems programming in{' '}
			<strong>Go</strong>, <strong>C</strong>, and <strong>Python</strong>; APIs and services built with current{' '}
			<strong>web frameworks</strong> where requirements go beyond a static site; <strong>automation</strong> including
			CI/CD integration, orchestration, and third-party integrations; and <strong>custom tooling</strong> such as
			CLIs, internal services, and data processing utilities. Emphasis on production-ready delivery, clear structure,
			and maintainability over time.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Observability &amp; automation</strong> — Grafana, metrics and logging pipelines, Kubernetes and Linux
			platforms; design and implementation of exporters, health checks, and automation integrated with your existing
			observability stack (see featured projects on the home page).
		</li>
	</ul>

	<p class="text-body-secondary mb-4">
		For a fuller picture of roles, certifications, and endorsements, review my
		<a href={CONTACT.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn profile</a>
		— and my
		<a href={`https://github.com/${GITHUB_USERNAME}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
		for public code and integrations.
	</p>

	<h2 class="h4 fw-bold mt-5 mb-3" id="inquire">Services inquiry</h2>
	<p class="text-body-secondary mb-4">
		Use the form below for <strong>scoped engagements</strong> across consulting, implementation, web, hosting,
		infrastructure, or development.
		It includes timeline, budget range, and scope so we can schedule a focused initial discussion. For general
		inquiries, use the <a href={hrefContact(pathname)}>contact form</a> or email{' '}
		<a class="fw-semibold" href={`mailto:${CONTACT.email}`}>{CONTACT.email}</a>.
	</p>

	<div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-5">
		<div class="card-body p-4">
			<ServicesInquiryForm />
		</div>
	</div>

	<p class="mb-0 d-grid gap-2 d-sm-flex flex-sm-wrap">
		<a class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm" href={hrefHome(pathname)}>← Home</a>
		<a class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm" href={hrefAbout(pathname)}>About</a>
		<a class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm" href={hrefBlog(pathname)}>Blog</a>
		<a class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm" href={hrefContact(pathname)}>Contact</a>
	</p>
</SimplePage>
